OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F442A1774361471
OL,3,CFisherman takes Lough Neagh fight to
OL,4,Ccourt
OL,6,FAn eel fisherman has taken Stormont's
OL,7,FDepartment for Agriculture,
OL,8,FEnvironment and Rural Affairs (DAERA)
OL,9,Fto court over the blue-green algae
OL,10,Fcrisis in Lough Neagh.
OL,12,FThe judicial review brought by Declan
OL,13,FConlon argues that the department is
OL,14,Fcontinuing to rely on 'inadequate
OL,15,Fplans' and 'unenforced pollution
OL,16,Fregimes', despite what's unfolded in
OL,17,Fthe lough over the last number of
OL,18,Fyears.
OL,20,FMr Conlon's family has fished Lough
OL,21,FNeagh for generations.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
